rComments: Prof. Grenier is my supervisor of the major research paper. He is the most popular prof for choosing a MRP supervisor. Very good reputation. Patient, nice, brilliant.

Doesn't use any technology in class. Tests are easy (especially the final, which consists in your choice of 7 questions out of 10) but he often seemed lost when he was teaching. Follows religiously the textbook. Overall, good prof.
c'est un bon professeur , il communique assez bien la matière. c'est un professeur attentionné. j'aime bien ce professeur :)
Notes are very unclear and not detailed. Doesn't speak loudly during class and mumbles a lot. Takes everything straight from the textbook, but doesn't do anything problem examples during class.
Very smart professor and if you work hard he will not trick you on the midterm. But he always give you a B and hardly an A. I loved his classes but a bit boring i have to admit.

He is really boring, so make sure that you sit at the front of the class.Easy assign.harder exams. he says he posts things on the internet, he does a poor job of it. for exams, make sure you look through old exams and find the multiple choice answers you dont know and study them with "google defined answers.
This prof doesn't seem comfortable teaching.  He always hesistates and stuff, but he does know his stuff bc does a lot of research in labour eco.
A great class with a great prof.
